sec.p:
Adult wild boar body mass correlated negatively with long-term (30-year) regional mean winter temperature (slope = -3.9, se = 1.1, 
  P < 0.001; 
  Fig 5). Males and females showed different intercepts (estimate = 25.7, se = 5.6, 
  P < 0.001; 
  Fig 5) but no difference concerning the slope of the relationship (
  P = 0.38; 
  Fig 5). Wild boars in the coldest region were about 30–40 kg (~ 30%) heavier than in the warmest region investigated.
